{% extends "layouts/standard_content.jinja" %}
{% from "components/card.jinja" import card %}
{% from "components/heading.jinja" import heading %}
{% from "components/contents.jinja" import contents %}
{% from "components/link.jinja" import link %}
{% from "components/list.jinja" import list, list_item %}
{% block mobile_article_title %}
  {% call heading() %}
    Apply for a licence
  {% endcall %}
{% endblock mobile_article_title %}
{% block desktop_article_title %}
  {% call heading() %}
    Apply for a licence
  {% endcall %}
{% endblock desktop_article_title %}
{% block article_navigation %}
  {% call contents(title="On this page") %}
    {% call list() %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#what-to-expect") %}
          What to expect
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#help-to-prepare") %}
          Help to prepare
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#apply-online") %}
          Apply online
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#after-you-apply") %}
          After you apply
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
    {% endcall %}
  {% endcall %}
{% endblock article_navigation %}
{% block article_content %}
  <p>Apply online to perform computational analysis on Find Case Law records.</p>
  <p>
    <strong>Important:</strong> You cannot save your application partway through. You will need to complete your application in one session.
  </p>
  <p>
    Make sure you have all the information you need before you begin. See
    {% call link(href=url("what_you_need_to_apply_for_a_licence")) %}
      What you need to apply for a licence
    {% endcall %}
    for details of the 29 questions we'll ask across 6 sections.
  </p>
  <p>You do not need to apply for a licence if your re-use is already covered under the Open Justice Licence.</p>
  <p>
    The Open Justice Licence covers most uses, including commercial use. You only need to apply if you want to perform computational analysis.
  </p>
  <p>
    See
    {% call link(href=url("when_you_need_permission")) %}
      When you need permission
    {% endcall %}
    if you're unsure whether you need to apply.
  </p>
  {% call heading(tag="h2") %}
    What to expect
  {% endcall %}
  {% call list(variant="bullets") %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      29 questions across 6 sections
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      you must complete the application in one session
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      some of your responses may be published in the future
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      it may take a few weeks until you receive a decision
    {% endcall %}
  {% endcall %}
  {% call heading(tag="h3") %}
    The 6 sections
  {% endcall %}
  {% call list(variant="decimal") %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      Contact details – The person responsible for the licence
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      Organisation details – Legal name and organisation type
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      Purpose and activities – What you intend to do (150 words)
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      Public statement – Summary for potential publication (150 words)
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      Working practices – Your methodology and ethical governance
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      Nine principles – Risk assessment against Ministry of Justice principles
    {% endcall %}
  {% endcall %}
  {% call heading(tag="h2") %}
    Help to prepare
  {% endcall %}
  <p>Download a full list of the 29 questions to prepare your answers before starting the application.</p>
  <p>
    {% call link(href=static('/documents/Dowloadable version of online application form reviewed 29_05.docx')) %}
      Download full list of 29 questions (Microsoft Word 29.2 kB)
    {% endcall %}
  </p>
  {% call heading(tag="h2") %}
    Apply online
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    {% call button(href=url("transactional-licence-form")) %}
      Apply for a licence
    {% endcall %}
  </p>
  {% call card(title="After you apply", title_tag="h2") %}
    {% call list(variant="bullets") %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        you will receive confirmation that we have received your application
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        your application will be assessed by the licence team
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        it will be reviewed by Discovery Board (meets monthly)
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        you'll be updated on the status of your application
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        it may be a few weeks until you receive a decision
      {% endcall %}
    {% endcall %}
    <p>
      Read more about the
      {% call link(href=url("licence_application_process")) %}
        Licence application process
      {% endcall %}
      .
    </p>
    <p>There are no costs to apply for a licence to perform computational analysis.</p>
    <p>
      If you have any questions about licensing, please email the Licensing Department:
      {% call link(href="mailto:caselawlicence@nationalarchives.gov.uk") %}
        caselawlicence@nationalarchives.gov.uk
      {% endcall %}
    </p>
  {% endcall %}
{% endblock article_content %}
